race.comment: CAELIUS (8) resumed over 1400m at Sale and hit the line sweetly to grab third, beaten half a length on that occasion. Getting to 1600m for the first time looks ideal for this Pierro colt and with even luck from a wide gate he can get the job done. KING TAGALOA (11) presents third up off two solid runs this time in, improving into the placings at Cranbourne in a handy maiden last start. He should be at peak fitness and will take catching. TAXING (4) is going okay, running a solid race at Echuca last time when sticking on for fourth. He gets every chance from the draw. ALWAYS TIRED (7) is a gelding by Justify on debut for the Freedman yard. He's been okay at the trials without lighting it up but the stable have to be respected. NECK HIGH (3) was good fresh with scope to improve.
